Source: orbita
Section: science
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Thomas Stibor <thomas@stibor.net>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9), cdbs, cmake, qt6-base-dev, libqt6opengl6-dev, libnova-dev
Standards-Version: 3.9.5
Homepage: https://github.com/tstibor/orbita
Vcs-Git: git://github.com/tstibor/orbita.git

Package: orbita
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libqt6opengl6, libqt6sql6-sqlite
Description: Simulate and visualize orbits of planets, comets and asteroids
 Orbita is a Qt6/OpenGL based program which renders our solar system in 3D.
 The Keplerian parameters are taken from the Minor Planet Center.
 Positions and orbits of planets, comets and asteroids are calculated by
 means of libnova library.

